**Notas:**
- `list.has(self.extra_signatories, d.owner)` verifica la firma del dueño.
- `assets.quantity_of(output.value, policy, name)` confirma que el NFT sigue presente, alineado con el principio CIP-0054 de que el NFT evoluciona enviándose a uno mismo.
- `output.value` se marca como `PLAUSIBLE_NEEDS_CHECK` ya que el acceso directo al campo `value` de `Output` no está explícitamente listado en las firmas verificadas.

## CIP-0054 Renderer Pattern

The `uses.renderer` field in CIP-0054 metadata allows many NFTs to point to a **single token that holds the rendering code**. Instead of embedding the same Javascript renderer in every NFT's metadata, each NFT stores only its input variables and declares which renderer to use. This massively reduces on-chain storage and duplication.

## Aiken Validator

To enforce that the renderer token is present as a reference input at spend time:

```aiken
use cardano/assets
use cardano/transaction.{Transaction, Input, OutputReference}
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}

validator smart_nft_renderer_check(
  renderer_policy: ByteArray,
  renderer_name: ByteArray,
) {
  spend(
    datum: Option<VerificationKeyHash>,
    _redeemer: Void,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    // Check renderer token is present in reference inputs
    let renderer_present =
      list.any(
        self.reference_inputs,
        fn(input: Input) {
          assets.quantity_of(
            input.output.value,
            renderer_policy,
            renderer_name,
          ) >= 1
        },
      )

    // Check owner signed (datum holds owner vkh)
    let owner_ok =
      when datum is {
        None -> False
        Some(owner) -> list.has(self.extra_signatories, owner)
      }

    renderer_present && owner_ok
  }

  else(_) {
    fail
  }
}
```

**Design notes:**
- `self.reference_inputs` lets the transaction include the renderer UTXO **without consuming it**, preserving it for all NFTs that reference it.
- `assets.quantity_of(input.output.value, ...)` checks the renderer token is in that reference input.
- `input.output.value` access is marked `PLAUSIBLE_NEEDS_CHECK` as nested field access on `Input.output` is not explicitly listed in the verified stdlib signatures.

