Hyperlane is a permissionless interoperability layer that computes cross-chain message IDs as `keccak256(message_body)`. Its multi-signature security module also verifies that a majority of off-chain validators have signed an ECDSA signature over a `keccak256` digest. By having `keccak_256` available in Plutus (CIP-0101), Cardano smart contracts can reproduce this ID computation on-chain and verify Hyperlane proofs natively.

Here is a simplified spend validator that checks a Hyperlane-style message ID:

```aiken
