This validator:
- Decodes the redeemer into a `CommitteeRedeemer` containing the list of expected signatories.
- Uses `list.all` to assert every provided `VerificationKeyHash` is present in `self.extra_signatories` via `list.has`.
- Returns `True` only when all signatories have signed, mirroring the all-of-k check underlying ATMS threshold logic.

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}
use cardano/transaction.{OutputReference, Transaction}

type CommitteeDatum {
  k: Int,
  committee: List<VerificationKeyHash>,
}

type CommitteeRedeemer {
  signers: List<VerificationKeyHash>,
}

validator atms_threshold {
  spend(
    datum: Option<CommitteeDatum>,
    redeemer: CommitteeRedeemer,
    _own_ref: OutputReference,
    self: Transaction,
  ) -> Bool {
    when datum is {
      None -> False
      Some(d) -> {
        let CommitteeRedeemer { signers } = redeemer
        let valid_signers =
          list.filter(
            signers,
            fn(vkh) {
              list.has(d.committee, vkh) && list.has(
                self.extra_signatories,
                vkh,
              )
            },
          )
        list.length(valid_signers) >= d.k
      }
    }
  }

  else(_) {
    fail
  }
}
```

Este validador:
- Lee el datum para obtener `k` (mínimo de firmantes) y la lista del comité autorizado.
- Filtra los firmantes del redeemer conservando sólo los que pertenecen al comité Y han firmado la transacción (`extra_signatories`).
- Verifica que el número de firmantes válidos sea al menos `k`, replicando la semántica k-de-t de ATMS.
